This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as grammatical error correction and text style transfer, which are typically categorized under the arXiv sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses sequence-to-sequence models, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, falling under the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Additionally, the paper uses regular language parallel data, which can be related to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) that deals with neural network-based approaches. Finally, the paper mentions the evaluation of the model on image captioning, which can be related to the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision) that deals with image and video processing.
